John S.D. Eisenhower, the son of President Dwight D. Eisenhower, has passed away. The President and Michelle Obama send their condolences to the Eisenhower family. John S.D. Eisenhower had a distinguished career as a soldier, serving in World War II and the Korean War, eventually retiring as a Brigadier General. He was also an accomplished writer, historian, and diplomat. His life was characterized by patriotism, character, learning, and service to his country. The Obamas offer their thoughts and prayers to John's wife, Joanne, his children, and grandchildren, along with gratitude for his extraordinary life.